## Component Breakdown

* Ingestion Gateway: Entry point for raw, heterogeneous menu formats (JSON, XML, HTML).
* Kafka Queue: Decouples heavy data extraction from core storage. Guarantees message delivery during ingestion spikes.
* LLM Translator & Currency Converter: Worker threads fetching real-time exchange rates and translating menu entities into target languages asynchronously.
* NoSQL Storage: Sharded by country and restaurant ID to ensure low-latency writes and horizontal scalability.
* Redis Cache: Stores fully compiled, localized menu objects at the edge to reduce database read pressure.
* Regional API Gateways: Direct client traffic to the nearest geographic data center, resolving localized content instantly based on IP coordinates.

